- "Highly accurate classification model" refers to machine learning models with an accuracy greater than 0.8;
- "Balanced cost" refers to the average cost per unit of materials.

- 'Predicts heat transfer coefficient based on temperature and velocity' refers to a specific type of model that calculates how heat is transferred under certain conditions;
- 'Active configurations' are system settings that are currently in use and not marked as inactive;
- 'Created by Jane Doe' specifies configurations that were set up by a user named Jane Doe;
- 'More expensive than the average' means the cost per unit of the material is higher than the average cost of all materials.

- "Density" refers to the mass per unit volume of a material;
- "Model accuracy" refers to the precision of a machine learning model in making predictions;
- "Configuration" represents a specific setup or arrangement of materials and models.

- 'Active system configurations' refer to configurations where the status is 'active';
- 'Average model accuracy' is calculated by averaging the accuracy values of all models associated with the material in active configurations;
